\title{Definition of an #{\mathcal{L}}-theory}
\date{2024-03-10}
\author{francis.westhead}
\taxon{definition}

\p{
    Given a [language](BMT-d001) #{\mathcal{L}}, a \em{#{\mathcal{L}}-theory} is a set of [#{\mathcal{L}}-sentences](BMT-d013). Sometimes it is notationally convenient to assume that theories are deductively closed.
}